The highly educated constitute an important part of the Democratic voter base. The party has strong support among scientists, with 55% identifying as Democrats, 32% as independents, and 6% as Republicans in a 2009 study.[228] Those with a college education have become increasingly Democratic in the 1992,[229] 1996,[229] 2000,[92] 2004,[93] and 2008[230] elections. In exit polls for the 2018 elections, 65% of those with a graduate degree said they voted Democratic, and Democrats won college graduates overall by a 20-point margin.[105]
